14.55: Pakistan get together for the huddle. They need a repeat performance from the first ODI. Small crowd at the Sheikh Zayed Stadium. Shoaib marks his run-up. It's also a very good evening to Peter English, Alex Malcolm and Raghav.

14.45: We're 15 minutes away from the start. Let's reflect on the series. It doesn't make good reading if you're a Pakistan fan - 1-3 down with a game to play. They will look back at the third ODI and blame it on the shocking collapse.

Nazia knocks on the door from UAE: "Best of luck Pakistan..and prove yourself that u are the best team..."

So Pakistan have only pride to play for in this dead rubber. Australia will be relieved to be in this position after a difficult ODI series in South Africa, which they lost.

Toss and teams: Australia have won the toss and they will bat first. They have made two changes - Nathan Bracken and Stuart Clark go out. The two Bens - Hilfenhaus and Laughlin - come in.

For Pakistan, Sohail Tanvir makes way for Umar Gul. That's it.

Australia: 1 Brad Haddin (wk), 2 Shane Watson, 3 Marcus North, 4 Michael Clarke (capt), 5 Andrew Symonds, 6 Callum Ferguson, 7 James Hopes, 8 Nathan Hauritz, 9 Ben Laughlin, 10 Ben Hilfenhaus, 11 Doug Bollinger.
